Reasoning: The paper deals with algorithmic information theory and the properties of entropy, which are topics that are commonly studied in the sub-category of information theory (cs.IT). The use of program-size complexity and the universal self-delimiting Turing machine suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The evaluation of randomness and convergence of the entropy measures may be of interest to researchers in the sub-category of computational complexity (cs.CC) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the study of entropy and randomness may also be relevant to the sub-category of cryptography (cs.CR).
